               <msContents>
                  <summary>Thirty-three Miracles of Mary, ተአምረ፡ ማርያም፡; Five Miracles of Michael, ተአምረ፡ ሚካኤል፡; Three Miracles of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus, ተአምረ፡ ገብረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡; Three Miracles of Jesus, ተአምረ፡ ኢየሱስ፡; One Miracle of Abunä Zär’a Buruk, ተአምረ፡ አቡነ፡ ዘርዓ፡ ቡሩክ፡</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="1r" to="43r"/><title type="complete" ref="LIT2384Taamme"/>
                     <note>
                    Thirty-Three Miracles of Mary.
                    <locus from="1r" to="7r"/>: Introductory Rite from Mu‘älläqa.
                    <locus from="8r" to="43r"/>: Thirty-three Miracles of Mary, each with a greeting
                    (beginning at: <locus target="#8r #9v #10v #11r #12r #13r #14r #15r #16r #16v #18v #19r #20r #20v #22r #22v #24r #25r #26r #26v #27v #29r #30r #30v #32r #34r #35r #36r #38v #39v #40v #41r #41v"/>).
                  </note>
                  </msItem>
               <msItem xml:id="ms_i2"><locus from="44r" to="47v"/>
                  <title>Five Miracles of Michael, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተአምረ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign> </title>
                  <note>
                    Each miracle with a greeting (beginning at: <locus target="#44r #44v #45v #46r #47r"/>.)
                    <locus from="44r" to="44v"/> How the Archangel Michael saved people in Egypt when their ship was caught in a storm in the middle of the sea.
                    <locus from="44v" to="45v"/> How the Archangel Michael appeared to a certain man who celebrated his feast every month, but in that season had lost his crops because of drought; how the Archangel Michael commanded him to go fishing and how he caught a great fish and found a chest of gold in the mouth of the fish.
                    <locus from="45v" to="46r"/>  How the Archangel Michael gave a blessing to a certain farmer who lost his crops to a devouring worm.
                    <locus from="46r" to="46v"/> How the Archangel Michael appeared to a devout man who was sick and how he healed him.
                    <locus from="47r" to="46v"/> How the Archangel Michael appeared at a certain church when a man possessed by an evil spirit came to the church and challenged the authority of the Archangel; and how the Archangel cured the man.
                  </note>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3"><locus from="47v" to="49v"/><title type="complete" ref="LIT3977Taammer"/>
                  <note>
                    <locus from="47v" to="48v"/> How Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus cast out a demon from a certain woman who suffered for three years from this evil spirit.
                    <locus from="48v" to="49r"/> How a certain man was on his way to the church during the feast of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus and a bird took his baptismal necklace of yarn (ማህተም); how the man beseeched the bird by the power of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus; and how, when he returned from the church, the bird was dead and the scarf was there (MYS 24, ff. 160rv).
                    <locus from="49r" to="49v"/>: How Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus raised a dead child when his mother prayer to the saint.
                  </note>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i4"><locus from="49v" to="52r"/><title type="complete" ref="LIT2382Taamme"/>
                  <note>
                    Three miracles beginning at <locus target="#49v #50r #51v"/>"
                  </note>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i5"><locus from="52v" to="56r"/>
                  <title>One Miracle of Abunä Zär’a Buruk, Tä’ammǝrä Abunä Zär’a Buruk, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተአምረ፡ አቡነ፡ ዘርዓ፡ ቡሩክ፡</foreign></title>
                  <note>
                  How, when Abunä Zär’a Buruk died, his spiritual children came from around the world, and many miracles occurred; and how many people were raised from the dead.
                  </note>
                </msItem>
